Portfolio

Elmer Ore

Nov 28th, 2020

Some of the analysis and projects I worked on.

Modeling

  1. Prediction Modeling demo: Predict the worthiness of credit applicants in a financial institution. Link to the presentation, and the Shiny application.
    Models tested: Generalized linear model, random forest and neural networks.
    Using: caret, recipes, ggplot2, dplyr, readxl, parallel, doParallel, shiny and shinythemes.

  2. Prediction modeling: predict the effectiveness of weight lifting using data from accelerometers.
    Model used: Random Forest.
    Using: dplyr, recipes, caret and parallel packages.

  3. Regression analysis comparing manual and automatic transmission over MPG performance.
    Using Akaike Information Criterion (AIC), Analysis of Variance (ANOVA) methods and Shapiro-Wilk test.

Statistics

  1. Hypothesis testing: adding statistical significance and confidence intervals to multiple A/B tests.
    Using: BigQuery, R and PowerBI.

  2. Statistical inference, describing the exponential distribution and its relationship with the Central Limit Theorem.

  3. Hypothesis testing, inferential analysis using the ToothGrowth dataset.

Data Analysis

  1. Descriptive analysis of the storms recorded by the U.S. National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administrations (NOAA) from 1950 to 2011. Report and source code of the analysis done.
    Tools: dplyr, ggplot2, maps.

  2. Locations where pedestrians can walk on the streets of Montreal with an interactive map using an open dataset from the city of Montreal.
    Using Leaflet

Visualization

  1. Introductory stock analysis for Top Food & Beverage companies
    Using R Markdown and Plotly.

Others

  1. Data manipulation and visualization of a personal activity monitoring device.
    Using dplyr and ggplot2.
